Mandera Governor Ali Roba has been bold in raising the red flag over the threat to key sectors like education.The Al-Shabaab resurgence provides room for novel counter-terrorism strategies and emergence of anti-terror champions In the recent past, there have been concerns that the Al-Shabaab menace is creeping back into the northeastern region, threatening law and order. Mandera County, which borders war torn Somalia, where the terrorists are domiciled, is most affected with increased attacks targeting both civilians and security personnel as well as destruction of infrastructure such as communication masts. 



