Mandera Governor Ali Roba has been bold and magnanimous in raising the red flag over the threat to key sectors like education. 

But every cloud has a silver lining. The Al-Shabaab resurgence provides room for novel counter-terrorism strategies and emergence of anti-terror champions. And Governor Roba fits the bill to spearhead that war. 

That he has admitted to there being a security problem gives him leeway to work towards addressing it. His call to residents to rise up against Al-Shabaab resonated well with not only local communities but the entire country. 



