Anti-terrorism war 

It is high time other leaders from Mandera, Garissa and Wajir followed in his footsteps. 

Kenyans need to heed such noble calls and be in the forefront in the anti-terrorism war for development to thrive. The ‘people power’ approach can prove to be mightier than government-based military approach. Soft power galvanises the population to roll out community initiatives, which have better results compared to State hard power. 

One such initiative is establishing a tamper-proof community reporting of suspicious activities, exposing Al-Shabaab’s modus operandi and identifying its sympathisers. Security personnel can use such actionable intelligence information to neutralise the threat. Residents can also volunteer to the National Police Reserve to help in the crackdown as they are more familiar with the terrain and other dynamics. 



