It is the civic duty of local communities to protect the country from external aggression and enable the region to prosper. Patriots must not succumb to threats to force submit to their criminal ideals. Let them reject in toto the tired and anachronistic rhetoric from Al-Shabaab, such as misplaced promises to ‘liberate’ Muslim lands and irredentist slogans that have no place in modern Kenya. 

The region is reaping the fruits of devolution. Colossal amounts of devolved, equalisation and other funds from the national government have revolutionised the region for the better. 

Quality services 

There is notable improvement in key sectors like health, infrastructure, water and education, to the extent that Somali nationals cross the border to enjoy the quality services offered in the counties. This is incomparable to Somalia, which is ravaged by terrorism and civil war. 

Our collective actions to counter terrorism will make Kenya a safe investment destination. The fight against terrorism is not a preserve of governments. 

The citizens, too, can actively participate in this worthy cause in many ways. Let everyone stand and be counted as a dependable ally in the anti-terror war. 



